annotationA: Protein dpy-30 homolog; Dpy-30-like 1 (Dpy-30L1) is part of the COMPASS complex, a histone H3K4 methyltransferase complex thought to be responsible for the bulk of the histone H3K4 di- and trimethylation in Drosophila. Dpy-30L1 binds to, and thereby inhibits, the metal-responsive transcription factor MTF-1
annotationB: Set1/Ash2 histone methyltransferase complex subunit ASH2; Transcriptional regulator. Regulates a number of genes involved in wing development including activation of net and bs and repression of rho and kni and controls vein-intervein patterning during wing development. Required for correct expression of a number of homeotic genes including Scr in the first leg imaginal disk and Ubx in the third leg imaginal disk and haltere disks.
